snippet.textDisplay: Couple of things. We have just played 3 home matches and won 1 of them. We lost to bottom of the league and struggled against the others. We are not ourselves while Celtic are blowing away 3rd in the league 4-0. I can't see who's going to take points off the tic to be honest and unfortunately that doesn't leave us in a very good place. Why does Gerrard persist with Aribo - he is absolute dog meat. Unacceptably bad, needs dropped instantly. I like the look of the young kid coming in - he took the game in his own hands last night. why was Katic dropped? Edmundson looked pretty decent but why not drop the 'irreplaceable' Goldson. I get so much fear when the ball is near him. Takes him 3 years to get turned and a further 5 to get back up from the ground - not good enough. Morelos is starting to lose the head again. League return is nowhere near Defoes in terms of minutes played I'm afraid and Defoe has more. Get Kamberi in for a bit.

snippet.textDisplay: A big hello from Romania to all Rangers fans! Please support Hagi, he's still young and he has some big shoes to fill, with his father's name on the back of that T-shirt! With your help, he might become a very good player. Genk and Fiorentina didn't use him too much and people didn't support him too much, mostly as he doesn't come from one of the big marketing countries like Spain, Italy, France or even UK. He might be an asset, so even when he has bad days, just support him. We need young players to write the future of football.
